$interpreted: Leah: So hot... This is probably the place, right?
Leah: Do you sell Moonstones?
Desert Merchant: Yes! Of course I do! I only sell top-quality Moonstones here too!
Desert Merchant: You can now get it for the cheap, cheap bargain price of 10000 Curren!
Leah: What!? 10000 Curren? That's highway robbery!
Leah: (That old hag told me that at most it's going to cost 5000 Curren...)
Leah: ...... Forget it. I'm not buying.
Desert Merchant: Little girl, you've been fiddling with that stone for a while already. Now you tell me you're not buying; I will be quite troubled!
Leah: Screw you, you shady merchant! I'm not afraid of you!
Desert Merchant: Miss! My bad, my bad! I give up!
Desert Merchant: You can have this for just 2000 Curren. I guarantee you, it's cost price!
Desert Merchant: Ah, right! You can have this for free as well. Buy one, get one free, right!
Leah: That's more like it. I'll accept your offer. See ya~
Fredrica: So you did manage to get it? Fabulous! You're much more capable than I imagined.
Fredrica: I just might offer you a great job opportunity once you graduate from the Academy~
Leah: Seriously!  Miss Lucien, you're not only beautiful on the outside, but you're beautiful on the inside as well~
Leah: You're indeed the most legendary, most stunning, most fabulous sorcerer the Academy has EVER seen!
Fredrica: Hoho~ You're stating the obvious~
Leah: What other ingredients do you need? I will find them all for you!
Leah: Here's the Moonstone you requested!
Fredrica: Ho? This Moonstone has a fine shine to it~
Fredrica: Oh, by the way, you have a package that has been forwarded to you by the Academy.
Leah: A package? For me?
Leah: (So a return gift from Lio and the guys? They must really love the Pomelodora I sent them~)
Leah: Eh? Isn't this the one I sent to them...
Leah: Sighs~ Is Lio still mad at me...
